news.title: Nashik civic body collects Rs 27 crore through amnesty scheme
news.para: The scheme attracted approximately 30,000 property tax defaulters, which resulted in the waiver of Rs 13 crore in penalties on their outstanding dues. The total property tax arrears stand at roughly Rs 450 crore, which includes Rs 200 crore in accumulated penalties.

news.title: Lucknow civic body's redressal camp resolves 48 property tax complaints
news.para: Municipal Commissioner Inderjit Singh oversaw the proceedings, ensuring that all issues were resolved on the spot. The LMC announced that these redressal camps would continue every Friday until all grievances are addressed.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body identifies 527 hazardous buildings, urges structural audits
news.para: ​​According to Section 265(a), buildings exceeding 30 years of usage require mandatory structural evaluation by an engineer registered with NMMC. The administration is actively encouraging prompt structural assessments of such properties.

news.title: Varanasi development body to use Geotrix software to detect illegal constructions
news.para: In view of this, experts from Advanced Satellite Transformation Software provided training to zonal officers and junior engineers about the new technology employed in the software's development

news.title: Mapusa police book eight for illegally selling Parra land to P K S Estate
news.para: “All persons fraudulently misrepresented themselves as legal heirs of the property before the lawful authority and then dishonestly carried out the documentary transaction in respect of the property at the office of the civil registrar cum sub registrar of Bardez, executed a sale deed, and accepted the amount towards the transaction,” police said.

news.title: Maharashtra pollution control board bans new ready-mix concrete plants in MMR
news.para: Existing plants will have to ensure anti-dust curtains at entry and exit gates, and undertake water sprinkling on vehicle tyres over the next three months.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC requests appointment as planning authority for slum redevelopment
news.para: "The UDD is once again requested to issue appropriate directions to appoint the BMC as the planning authority for the redevelopment of slums on BMC lands under 64 specific schemes, as well as for all other slum rehabilitation projects on BMC lands, except ongoing SR schemes managed by the SRA.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to auction tax defaulters’ properties from December 2
news.para: Defaulters, especially those owning non-residential properties, who fail to clear dues even though One Time Settlement (OTS) scheme was introduced nine months ago, are certain to face the music, civic officials said

news.title: House of Abhinandan Lodha buys American Center in Mumbai for over Rs 56 crore
news.para: However, the structure spread over nearly 1,400 sq meters or one-third of an acre has been lying vacant for the past decade after the US consulate shifted from south Mumbai to the business district of Bandra-Kurla Complex (BKC).

news.title: Benefits of central schemes like PMAY not reaching tribals: President
news.para: "Being a tribal myself, I understand your plight and concerns and also your education system. The Central Government has initiated measures to bring the tribals including the PVTG into the national mainstream," Murmu said during her maiden visit to Udhagamandalam.

news.title: Goa police issue look out circular against seven individuals in share market scam
news.para: The EOC has booked five directors of a real estate company in connection with a case in the ‘stock market’ scam. Rodrigues and his wife Deepali Parab allegedly cheated people, mostly from Salcete, of over Rs 100 crore by promising lucrative returns on investments in the share market.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso's builder seeks approval for phase-wise redevelopment
news.para: If accepted, the builder will be able to reconstruct the towers declared unsafe at the Sector 109 society in one phase and repair the ones considered habitable in another.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth Rs 1.56 crore of Samson and Sons Builders and Developers
news.para: As part of the ongoing probe, the ED has provisionally attached 13 properties belonging to the accused, including 12 parcels of land and a residential flat located in Pattom and Karakulam, Thiruvananthapuram.

news.title: SC orders re-evaluation of Orissa HC's ruling in Bhubaneswar land scam case
news.para: Hearing the appeal filed by state govt, SC in its recent order observed that the realtors used their connections to manipulate land records

news.title: I-T searches on Gujarat's builder group on suspicion of tax evasion
news.para: The searches on 34 residential and commercial premises were conducted in Ahmedabad, Gandhinagar, Mehsana, and Morbi, among others. Out of the total, 25 were in Ahmedabad alone.

news.title: Gujarat: Proposed 900% increase in draft jantri rates alarms builders
news.para: The draft rates were introduced months after a previous rate doubling in 2023. In many developing areas, the rate increases from 2023 could reach 2,000%, raising concerns about land deals and project costs.

news.title: Brookfield to sell two São Paulo malls to Iguatemi for $410 million: Sources
news.para: The companies have just set the price for the majority stakes Brookfield owns in malls Patio Paulista and Patio Higienopolis, aiming to finalize a deal by the end of December, a deadline that may be slightly extended due to the year-end holidays, two of the sources said this week.

news.title: Vasai-Virar civic body razes 41 illegal structures in Nalasopara
news.para: ​​There are 41 illegally constructed buildings and other structures in Nalasopara, and the court has ordered the authorities to pull them down.

news.title: Primarc & RDB Group to buy business undertaking of DLF Techpark 1 for Rs 638 crore
news.para: JLL was the transaction advisor to both parties. Fox & Mandal were the legal advisors to RDB & Primarc. Shardul Amarchand Mangaldas & Co and PwC were the legal and financial advisors respectively to DLF.
